T1  - Toward a theory of bank loan commitments
AU  - Thakor, Anjan V.
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 6
IS  - 1
SP  - 55
EP  - 83
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/03/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(82)90022-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842668290022X
AB  - The characteristics of fixed and variable rate bank loan commitments are analyzed in a contingent-claims framework, and valuation expressions are derived for these commitments. The valuation expressions are used to present estimates of the impact of interest rate uncertainty on the liability assumed by a bank issuing loan commitments. Finally, a simple, two-period, asymmetric information model is employed to explain the recent trend among bankers to substitute variable rate commitments for their fixed rate counterparts.
ER  - 
